content:
Most demons understand the game of chess. Demons respect chess. It is a game of light and darkness. And chess resembles centuries and centuries of war, domination, pillaging, death, destruction, and carnage. Demons are experts at playing chess. They understand the game, they know every move there could ever be in the game of chess.

Playing chess doesn't create a dark energy. At the same time, chess is highly revered by demons. If anything, demons will have more respect for an individual who plays chess and will be less likely to cause a problem. Which is why playing chess, or even simply having a chess board in your home, is a surprising Spiritual Light of Free Will against demons.

If you think there's some demon influence happening in people around you, or things are seemingly very difficult for you, getting on a chess board is a tool. It's a weapon against darkness because it instantly perplexes any kind of demon energy. To the demon, it means you're in control. You take control of the grid.

Once you know what your well-intentioned purpose is in playing chess beyond just playing the game, it becomes a true device into the supernatural, both advancing and strengthening Light and understanding and defeating darkness.

The chess board itself and the pieces are demon deterrents. Having a chess game in your home on the coffee table—or somewhere out of reach if you have pets or little ones—is far more effective than sage-ing when it comes to demons. The chess board indicates that demons have already lost. It's a reminder of the harm they caused when they were in human form, that they lost in the game of life and after-death. And it's a reminder that you have the ability to outsmart them.

When demons see the chess board, they immediately see information going back centuries on evildoings during battles and wars, and they know that they've always been on the wrong side, which eventually becomes the losing side—because God, who they're afraid of, rules all. You're instantly winning just by playing the game itself.
